'''''Jedi Dawn''''' is a "choose your own adventure"&ndash;style roleplaying book, written by [[Paul Cockburn]] and published, in the United Kingdom only, by [[Boxtree]] in [[1993]]. It was the first part of [[The Lost Jedi]] adventure game series. The story was later collected along with ''[[The Bounty Hunter]]'' in ''[[The Lost Jedi Adventure Game Book]]''.

==Plot summary==
In [[1 BBY/Legends|1 BBY]], [[Havet Storm]] inherits his grandfather's [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] and discovers that he has within him the potential to become a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]]. Running from the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] agents that killed his family, Havet arrives on the planet [[Toprawa/Legends|Toprawa]], location of a high-security Imperial Research Station. Shortly after arriving on the planet, Storm makes a personal enemy of [[Boba Fett/Legends|Boba Fett]] and becomes embroiled in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance's]] attempts to steal the plans to a frightening new Imperial [[Death Star/Legends|superweapon]].

